.TH LIBNETDIAG 3 "July 2026" "libnetdiag 0.2" "Library Functions Manual"
.SH NAME
libnetdiag \- pure C syscall-free network diagnostics state machine library
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include <netdiag.h>
.PP
.B ping_ctx *ping_create(netdiag_role_t role);
.br
.B int ping_feed_input_with_ts(ping_ctx *ctx, const uint8_t *data, size_t len, uint64_t now_ms);
.br
.B int ping_process(ping_ctx *ctx, uint64_t now_ms);
.br
.B int ping_next_event(ping_ctx *ctx, netdiag_event_t *event);
.br
.B int ping_get_stats(ping_ctx *ctx, netdiag_stats_t *stats);
.SH DESCRIPTION
libnetdiag provides deterministic, callback-free, syscall-free state machines for emulating and analyzing common network diagnostics tools (ping, arping, traceroute, DNS) on edge devices.
.PP
All I/O, timestamps, and policy decisions remain in the calling application.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR netdiag(3),
.BR ping(1),
.BR arping(8)